<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 07 at 1:27PM MDT until July 07 at 2:30PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Great Falls has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Glacier County in north central Montana...
* Until 230 PM MDT.
* At 127 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 15 miles northwest
of North Browning, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
northeastern Glacier County.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
